`docs/` is project-level reference material outside the auto-generated context tree: decision history, a task backlog, and speculative design notes for tooling that doesn't exist yet. Nothing here is derived from `ctx-context` or kept in sync automatically — each file has its own update discipline and none of them describe current source architecture (that lives in rollups/`intent.md` elsewhere).

The three files serve different questions and shouldn't be conflated: `DECISIONS.md` answers *why* (append-only ADR log, never rewrite, supersede via new entries), `STATUS.md` answers *what's left* (hand-maintained, impact-sorted backlog with file:line references that go stale on their own and aren't auto-fixed), and `DYLINT_RULES.md` answers *what's planned* (nine unimplemented lint rules, several overlapping with live scripts in `scripts/` — `rationale_check.py` and `cycle_check.sh` — that must stay in sync until the dylint versions actually supersede them).

A cross-file trap: `DECISIONS.md` records that `docs/SPEC.md` was retired to `docs/retired/SPEC.md` (ADR-052) and its content redistributed; don't treat SPEC.md as a live target for new normative writing, and don't be surprised if `STATUS.md` or `DYLINT_RULES.md` reference concepts that used to live there. Similarly, `STATUS.md` deliberately omits one known finding (`.context` orphan-reconciliation) because it's being handled elsewhere — don't re-add it without checking status first.

No `intent.md` exists for this directory, so no divergence check applies.